description.0: The Indestructible Man’s tearing through San Francisco and nothing can stop him! It’s up to Daredevil and Black Widow to try, but how do you defeat the Indestructible Man?
description.3: Rhino becomes the ultimate wedding crasher- at the nuptials of Betty Ross and Glenn Talbot! Plus, the Leader's master plan careens Hulk and Rhino towards Counter-Earth. Will the two combatants remain trapped on this faraway planet?
description.4: Iron Man battle with Raga continues! Will Tony Stark be able to overcome the fiery forces of the living volcano? Or has his luck run out when the Black Lama appears! The fate of man rests in his hands!
description.6: The Thunder God meets a worthy opponent- the Absorbing Man strikes again!
description.7: The Human Torch quits the FF! The Thing embattled! Plus, the return of the Frightful Four- starring a nefarious new recruit.
description.12: Jungle adventure - with a twist! And an awesome origin that'll move and shake you!
description.13: Curly of the Satan's Saints prepares Roxanne as a sacrificial vessel! Johnny discovers Curly's plot a little too late…
description.14: Longing to ride the skies once more, the Defenders assist Silver Surfer in leaving Earth. While dimension-hopping, the team encounters the Nameless Ones! Plus, the liberation of Barbara Norris!
description.17: Can Ka-Zar keep his promise to protect Dr. Calvin while he ends up in a turf war with the Pusher? Meanwhile, the truth is revealed about Calvin's son…
description.18: Spider-Man's been knocked unconscious...by Aunt May?!
description.19: Iron Man, Black Panther, Hawkeye and Scarlet Witch search the entire city of New York for a lead on Quicksilver. The Vision remains behind brooding over Wanda and the Grim Reaper's offer, but his love-worn thoughts are soon interrupted by Captain America.
description.20: This one has the Falcon seeing double: Captain America takes on the Captain America from the 1950s!
description.21: Haunted by a nightmare of nuclear holocaust, and given the location of the Project Four sphere, Damon Dran suits up and becomes…the Indestructible Man! Elsewhere, Black Widow is under some kind of mystic control and turns on Daredevil. The couple duke it out, but can Daredevil subdue his romantic partner without causing her harm?
description.22: The Spawn of Sligguth reveals its plan - to resuurect Shuma-Gorath!
description.26: THE CAT STALKS AT NIGHT. In her first Marvel Universe appearance, we learn the origin of Greer Grant and her unusual role in an experiment. Enter...The Cat!
description.27: Spider-Man and the VISION, together in an exciting adventure! The mysterious mechanical creature known as the MONSTROID is terrorizing the city! Can the Wall-Crawler and the Android Avenger take it down - and find the mysterious entity pulling its strings?
description.28: Hammerhead gives the Wallcrawler an ultimatum: join his gang or die!
description.29: Scarlet Witch has locked herself in the Avengers' control room and will not leave until she finds clues about her missing brother. Meanwhile, Black Panther returns from a strange mission with Daredevil.
description.30: Prepare for the never-before-see secret origin of Captain America!
description.31: BEWARE THE LIVING H BOMB! Megaton is here and it's up to Rick and Captain Marvel to stop him before it's too late!
description.33: Critically injured from Quasimodo, the Beast can't catch a break as he faces a new villain...the Griffin!
description.36: The first appearance of Night Nurse!  When Christine Palmer picks up the night shift at Metro-General Hospital, things get dangerous…
description.38: The Rhino returns, but he's not the one calling the shots! Bruce laments his loss with Betty Ross, as Betty prepares to wed Glenn Talbot. Plus, what's the Leader up to?
description.39: Iron Man is no match for Raga, son of fire! Armor melts like wax, steel runs like water before the living volcano! Witness Iron Man great's defeat!
description.41: The Thunder God vs. Mephisto...in the haunted halls of the Sub-World! And the demon's allies are none other than Thor's most trusted friends- including the Lady Sif.
description.43: The battle to the finish with Mole Man! And with Mole Man's marriage on the line, this fight's sure to be heated. Will the FF become prisoners in Subterranea?
description.46: Black Widow has left Daredevil without a word and our horned hero is furious about it! DD prowls the streets of San Fran looking for clues to Black Widow’s whereabouts. Little does he know, Widow’s been captured by Damon Dran, and is being prepped for torture!
description.49: It's Hulk vs. Hulk- to the death! But one of our green-skinned goliaths has the brain of...Bruce Banner?
description.50: He's stood against titans and Titanium Man, but can the Iron Man stand against the onslaught of Cyborg Sinister's axe?
description.52: Mephisto returns! And still trapped on Earth, Tana Nile enhances her Earthling disguise. But will Odin be fooled?
description.53: The ever-lovin' Thing fights Mole Man alone! But where's the rest of the crew? And, more mind-staggering artwork by John Buscema!
description.59: Silver Surfer joins the fray! Plus, a Strange adventure in the Himalayas...in a valley of apes!
description.60: Spider-Man gets caught up in the middle of war between Doc Ock and Hammerhead.
description.61: Quicksilver and Larry Trask must team-up to destroy rogue Sentinels that are planning on firing solar flares to destroy Earth's mutants. But is Trask the man he claims to be? And who is the rightful hero of the day?
description.62: The Avengers want Captain America, dead or alive!
description.63: The spirit of Crash Simpson, Blaze's father figure, rises! The Satan's Saints biker gang may have stronger ties to the occult than Blaze imagined, especially when their leader, Curly, starts dabbling in ritual sacrifice!
description.66: Terror in the Everglades! Perhaps the greatest Ka-Zar saga of all, as the jungle lord comes face-to-face with…the Man-Thing!
description.68: He's back from the dead! Mr. Fear, the only man who knows Daredevil’s true identity. Matt Murdock better watch his back.
description.69: No good deed goes unpunished! Doctor Strange learns this the hard way, when helping an old friend turns into a fight for his life!
description.70: Enter the awesome entity called the Shaper of Worlds! All of reality is threatened by this latest foe. And if that weren't enough, a Nazi war criminal makes his villainous debut: introducing Captain Axis!
description.71: Iron Man battles Princess Python, whose pet python move to her command at the speed of thought! Is Tony Stark's Iron suit a match for the massive python's' hold?
description.73: Ego Prime defeated! Odin's master plan revealed at last! Then as one chapter closes...a new mystery begins.
description.75: The return of the Mole Man! And the FF will never see him coming. Plus, the incredible original of Marvel's First Family re-told.
description.79: Spidey's team-up this time around is with the X-MEN! But this is no team-up...it's a showdown! Why are the heroic mutants attacking Spider-Man!?
description.81: Give it up, Beast! Even you can't survive the deadly attack of Quasimodo - the computer that kills!
description.85: Spidey uncovers a clue as to the whereabouts of his missing Aunt May.
description.86: With the Scarlet Witch kidnapped, and Quicksilver missing, the Avengers suspect that their mutant teammates are being targeted. But who is behind the madness? Perhaps it's Larry Trask, the new director of the Sentinel Program!
description.88: The hero that wouldn't die...IS BACK! Featuring, the mind-boggling menace of Megaton, the atomic assassin!
description.89: The mysteries of Project Four! But, what happens when the Man Without Fear becomes…a coward? Cold fear seizes Black Widow- but why?
description.92: The astonishing Ant-Man guest-stars! Plus, the Chameleon and the many hordes of Hydra! Hulk shrinks to a subatomic level to find Jarella...but what does this mean for Betty Ross?
description.93: The fate of Iron Man is revealed! Will Marianne Rodger's most dreaded revelation come to past? Will the Adaptoid be the end of Tony Stark?
description.96: This is it! The battle to the finish with Ego Prime!
description.97: The secret of the Monster revealed! Can Human Torch and Thing thwart the creature's attack before they, and the planet, perish? Plus, what does this creature really need from Earth?
description.98: Kraven the Hunter enters the fray! Can Spidey handle him AND the Gibbon?
description.99: The Vision travels to a frozen food storage facility to hear out a proposition from the Grim Reaper. Will the Vision prove to be a less-than reliable teammate once again?

11.text: Namor stands alone against the hideous Haab, an underwater race intent on the deaths of all Atlanteans. But will they succeed? This is one surprise ending that shakes Namor to his core!

15.text: A supernatural being dubbed the 'Phantom of 45th Street' creeps into the Gem Theater! Luke Cage wakes to a fight he cannot win. The following day, Cage is hired to investigate the Phantom by someone else who has also been haunted. Can Luke uncover the secret of the Phantom before another night of midnight mischief?

16.text: Jennifer Kale is an amateur witch, a young woman still unfamiliar with her ties to the occult. What bond will be forged between Jennifer and Man-Thing? And when Jennifer accidentally unleashes the Nether-Spawn, will help come all too late?

34.text: Hank Pym finally gets home after a trying couple of days -- only to discover his wife, Janet, unconscious on the floor!

35.text: Jack discovers the plans of Mark Cephalos - the man behind the helicopter attack on the Werewolf!

36.text: When Linda Carter picks up the night shift at Metro-General Hospital things get dangerous...

42.text: Dracula uses the magical black mirror to travel back in time to 19th century Transylvania to undertake a nefarious mission!

58.text: Sunfire's pride may be wounded, but he and Namor must set aside differences or stand defeated by Dragon-Lord! Plus: Namor is accosted by Atlantis' mutant population. Will the ruler of the seas be able to forge peace between Atlantis and her mutant citizens?

63.text: The Ghost Rider meets the Satan's Saints bikers!

64.text: Luke Cage is visited by Owen Ridgley, a man who informs the Hero for Hire about a terrorist plot. Gideon Mace plans on blowing up each bridge and power station in Manhattan! His goal? To shake the very foundation of the United States! And Luke Cage is running out of time.

65.text: Man-Thing - all fear burns at its touch.  When a young child is in danger, will Man-Thing exact justice upon the child's evil father?

66.text: Swamp Tank tries to steal Ka-Zar's vibranium!

74.text: Dracula returns to Castle Dracula to reclaim what is rightfully his!

78.text: The battle to the finish with Sunfire! And, you've never seen anything quite like Dragon-Lord!

82.text: After being drugged and kidnapped, Hank Pym is now stuck in a three-inch body. And things only get harder when he stumbles into Egghead, his longtime enemy!

83.text: Jack Russell, A.K.A. the Werewolf by Night, befriends Buck Cowan. But can Jack save his new friend and his sister Lissa from the stone-cold stare of Marlene Blackgar?
